The '''Gateway Protection Programme''' is a scheme operated by the British government in partnership with the [[United Nations High Commissioner for Refugees]] (UNHCR) and co-funded by the [[European Union]] (EU), offering a legal route for a quota of UNHCR-identified [[refugee]]s to settle in the United Kingdom.

